criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. Must be diagnosed with CP according to National standard criteria including clinical history and physical examination;
2. Aged between 2 and 14 years;
3. No prior history of epilepsia gravior within 15 days of infusion and no seizures attack within 24 hours of treatment;
4. Must be able to comply with scheduled visits, treatment plans, physical examinations, laboratory tests, performance scales, and other study procedures;
5. Showed willingness by signing the informed consent form, which was approved by the IRB for patients or parents.
